1
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:34,920
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,810
[Episode 9]

3
00:01:39,039 --> 00:01:39,870
You know what?

4
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:41,710
Visiting Beijing is no big deal.

5
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:42,560
I just went there casually!

6
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,610
What's so special about it?

7
00:01:43,610 --> 00:01:44,759
Where have you been?

8
00:01:44,789 --> 00:01:45,710
We went to that...

9
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:48,150
When I was little, I got sick of visiting
the Forbidden City, Tiananmen,

10
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:50,090
Wangfujing, the Yuanmingyuan Park,
the Yihe Garden,

11
00:01:50,090 --> 00:01:51,690
and the Badaling Great Wall.

12
00:01:51,789 --> 00:01:53,430
Locals don't even like
going to those places.

13
00:01:53,430 --> 00:01:54,330
Which places did you visit?

14
00:01:54,330 --> 00:01:54,920
Where did you visit?

15
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,950
-Tell us where you've been.
-Where have you been?

16
00:01:56,950 --> 00:02:00,150
Beijing just has those scenic spots.
The Forbidden City,

17
00:02:00,150 --> 00:02:01,000
Tiananmen,

18
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:02,310
Wangfujing,

19
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:03,570
the Yihe Garden,

20
00:02:03,950 --> 00:02:05,550
and the Badaling Great Wall.

21
00:02:05,710 --> 00:02:07,310
What's the point of going there?

22
00:02:07,310 --> 00:02:08,870
You didn't go, did you?

23
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:09,710
Bragger.

24
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,450
Hey, if locals don't go, why should I?

25
00:02:11,450 --> 00:02:12,660
Then what did you do?

26
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,650
I went to that school first.

27
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:16,800
Their campus is huge,

28
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:17,730
much better than ours.

29
00:02:17,730 --> 00:02:18,660
What's more,

30
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,160
I met a legendary figure there.

31
00:02:21,180 --> 00:02:22,520
-Who?
-A legendary figure?

32
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,590
Their school's... that... that...

33
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:25,890
Security guard.

34
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:28,460
What's so special about a security guard?

35
00:02:28,460 --> 00:02:30,120
Why do you look down on security guards?

36
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,750
That guard's exceptionally capable.

37
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:32,630
-He's awesome.
-That's all?

38
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:33,280
Anything else?

39
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:33,800
Yeah.

40
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:36,400
Then we went to a mysterious alley.

41
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:39,250
They say there's an old lady
in that alley.

42
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:42,220
Whoever meets her
gets their souls hooked away.

43
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:43,440
I met her.

44
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:44,800
Judge Ma'am?

45
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,540
So basically, you just didn't go anywhere.

46
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:48,000
What are you so smug about?

47
00:02:48,570 --> 00:02:49,630
What do you mean, I didn't go anywhere?

48
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:50,910
I've been to a whole lot of places!

49
00:02:50,910 --> 00:02:52,680
-Well...
-Then how did Xiaodan do on the exam?

50
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,570
What do you mean by "how she did"?

51
00:02:53,570 --> 00:02:54,290
Look at you.

52
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:57,000
So snobbish. Isn't the process important?

53
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,960
The process is more amazing, you know?

54
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:01,420
Oh, no,
sounds like she didn't pass the exam.

55
00:03:02,210 --> 00:03:03,740
What are you talking about?

56
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:04,710
Look.

57
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:05,780
Xiaodan...

58
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:06,710
X-Xiaodan.

59
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:07,800
Well.

60
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:09,750
Take a look.

61
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:10,470
See?

62
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:11,330
What did I say?

63
00:03:12,310 --> 00:03:13,370
What did I tell you?

64
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:17,000
She didn't pass.
She was just there enjoying the process.

65
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,660
What's wrong with your class?

66
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:20,910
I walked over from there,

67
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:21,910
and your class is the only noisy one.

68
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,170
What class is this? Where is the teacher?

69
00:03:24,710 --> 00:03:26,520
Director Hou, Mr. Gu is sick.

70
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:28,310
We're having self-study this period.

71
00:03:28,310 --> 00:03:28,750
Right.

72
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,560
Self-study.

73
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,620
Do you know what "self-study" means?

74
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:34,210
Class president, maintain some order.

75
00:03:34,210 --> 00:03:34,800
Alright, alright.

76
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,870
Go back to your seats. Go back.

77
00:03:35,870 --> 00:03:37,630
-Let's go back.
-Class is starting.

78
00:03:37,630 --> 00:03:40,630
Xiaoman, Ms. Tong is sick,

79
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:42,310
and Ms. Dai is also under the weather.

80
00:03:42,310 --> 00:03:43,960
Is there a flu going around our school?

81
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,280
It's not the flu.

82
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,160
Don't you know?

83
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,520
Our teachers were almost all

84
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:50,320
taken out by the royal jelly
from Xia Lei's family.

85
00:03:58,870 --> 00:03:59,930
What are you doing?

86
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:02,050
Who are you throwing a tantrum at?

87
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:04,560
What am I doing? It's
all because of this lousy royal jelly.

88
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,280
It made all our teachers sick.

89
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:07,560
Now the whole grade's students are
blaming me

90
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,960
and this junk royal jelly
our family makes.

91
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:10,150
Watch your tone with your mother!

92
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:12,800
She works hard all day

93
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,150
and has to sell royal jelly
when she gets home at night.

94
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:16,279
What for? Isn't it for your education?

95
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:18,000
To earn some money for our family!

96
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,000
And here you are, yelling at us.

97
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,750
You sell this lousy royal jelly
to make money?

98
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:22,830
It's a shoddy product.

99
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:24,360
Y-You're talking back to me now?

100
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,630
H-How was I supposed to know...

101
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:26,560
If I knew it was shoddy,

102
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,510
would I... would I have
stocked up on it? Honestly.

103
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:30,000
Your mother was scammed, too!

104
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,330
It's okay. D-Don't cry.

105
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:34,000
You brat. We are victims, too!

106
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,070
Stop yapping!

107
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:37,600
Besides, we didn't sell many boxes.

108
00:04:37,630 --> 00:04:39,240
We've bought back the few we sold,

109
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,240
you know?

110
00:04:40,270 --> 00:04:40,800
Well...

111
00:04:40,830 --> 00:04:41,510
What?

112
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:45,000
Nothing. I... I was just asking.

113
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,330
Did you get your answer?

114
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,060
Go! If you get it, go do your homework.

115
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,510
We'll call you for dinner.

116
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:54,710
Mom, don't get upset.

117
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,620
I-It's none of your business.

118
00:04:55,620 --> 00:04:56,680
Stay o-out of this.

119
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:58,750
Go, just go!

120
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:03,710
Brat, how could you yell at your mother?

121
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:08,830
Was that okay, Honey?

122
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,690
Did I show enough authority

123
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:12,730
as the head of the family just now?

124
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,630
Why were you so harsh with our son?

125
00:05:14,630 --> 00:05:15,890
Why were you so fierce?

126
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,390
H-He was yelling at you.

127
00:05:17,510 --> 00:05:18,360
Okay, okay.

128
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,630
Then I... I'll go apologize to him.

129
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,510
That's not necessary.

130
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:23,120
Save it.

131
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,450
Just watch it next time.

132
00:05:25,410 --> 00:05:26,450
Don't drink that.

133
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,120
It'll be a waste.

134
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,630
What if you get diarrhea?

135
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,630
That's like suicide.

136
00:05:32,830 --> 00:05:33,960
It is a bit of a waste.

137
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:39,070
If we get sick, we get sick together.

138
00:05:39,220 --> 00:05:40,980
Alright. It's okay.

139
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:42,180
Let it go.

140
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:43,680
Oh, my...

141
00:05:50,770 --> 00:05:51,630
Studying hard?

142
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,850
What brings you here?

143
00:05:53,850 --> 00:05:56,180
Nothing really. Are your parents asleep?

144
00:05:58,550 --> 00:06:00,010
At this hour? Definitely.

145
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,580
The weather's nice today.

146
00:06:05,410 --> 00:06:06,270
Let me take you out for a walk

147
00:06:06,270 --> 00:06:07,330
to clear your head.

148
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:09,680
Nice.

149
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:10,400
Let's go.

150
00:06:17,630 --> 00:06:19,490
Why don't you go to sleep at night?

151
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:21,210
I don't want to.

152
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:24,840
The plant is full of people
during the day.

153
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,240
Too noisy.

154
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,420
That is everyone's East Chemical Plant.

155
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:33,120
At night, everyone's off work and home.

156
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,159
There's no one left in the plant.

157
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,310
That is my East Chemical Plant.

158
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:39,010
I hold sway over this place.

159
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:43,430
So free.

160
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:45,870
I'm envious, really.

161
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:49,120
I walk on the pipes
whenever I'm free at night.

162
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,270
There are countless pipes in our plant,

163
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:52,750
reaching every nook and cranny,

164
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:54,480
making it easy to get anywhere.

165
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,610
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]

166
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,400
You'd better be careful.

167
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,070
Those ladders are rusty.

168
00:06:58,070 --> 00:06:59,750
Don't miss a step and fall.

169
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:02,130
How do you know the ladders are rusty?

170
00:07:02,330 --> 00:07:03,650
It's been so many years

171
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,740
since our plant had any maintenance.

172
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:08,430
You really are a smart one.

173
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:11,020
What do they call people like you?

174
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,820
A scholar who never leaves home,

175
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:17,050
yet knows everything about the world.

176
00:07:18,810 --> 00:07:20,130
I'm different.

177
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,160
People like me...

178
00:07:24,830 --> 00:07:26,230
People like me

179
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:31,240
won't realize anything

180
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:34,360
until the eleventh hour,

181
00:07:35,950 --> 00:07:39,480
until it's right in front of my face.

182
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,940
What's wrong with you?

183
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:48,920
Nothing.

184
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:53,040
I just wander around at night
when I'm free.

185
00:07:53,990 --> 00:07:56,040
Just roam around. But sometimes,

186
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,000
I keep walking

187
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,630
and end up reaching Xiaodan's place.

188
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,160
Since I'm already there,

189
00:08:04,130 --> 00:08:06,790
I'd sit on the heating pipes
to keep her company.

190
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,540
But the pipes are so close to her house

191
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:14,870
that I can hear Chief Engineer Yan
talking inside.

192
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:16,190
And then?

193
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:17,950
Then...

194
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:20,510
And then?

195
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,360
Chief Engineer Yan's transfer order
has been issued.

196
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,960
He's going back to Shanghai.

197
00:08:30,050 --> 00:08:31,850
Xiaodan is supposed to move back

198
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:33,880
after the college entrance exam.

199
00:08:35,669 --> 00:08:37,059
So this time, they'll go back to Shanghai

200
00:08:37,059 --> 00:08:38,990
not just to visit their relatives?

201
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:55,030
Xiaodan...
Xiaodan is going back to Shanghai.

202
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,960
And you,

203
00:08:58,030 --> 00:08:59,910
you're off to college.

204
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,480
I'll be the only one left.

205
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:09,930
You...

206
00:09:10,730 --> 00:09:11,670
Don't be so pessimistic.

207
00:09:11,670 --> 00:09:13,200
You've still got Dongdong.

208
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,360
Don't be down.

209
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,690
Who says going to college is the only way

210
00:09:19,690 --> 00:09:21,200
to get out of the East Chemical Plant?

211
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,730
You can also get a job out of town
in the future.

212
00:09:23,940 --> 00:09:25,900
Y-You're going to college.

213
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:28,630
Have you decided where to apply?

214
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:29,430
Is it far away?

215
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:33,780
I also have no idea.

216
00:09:35,010 --> 00:09:36,030
I don't know where these tracks

217
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:37,230
will lead me, either.

218
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:45,350
Haven't you ever thought about going out
to see the world?

219
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:47,750
No, I haven't.

220
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:49,210
I think our plant is great.

221
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:51,550
Right? It's comfortable.

222
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:54,360
Besides,

223
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:58,160
no matter how fast or far a train runs,

224
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:01,960
it goes out along the tracks,

225
00:10:02,770 --> 00:10:04,900
and it has to come back sooner or later,

226
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,000
right?

227
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:10,410
Won't you guys come back after you go off

228
00:10:11,910 --> 00:10:12,750
to college?

229
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,720
You mean, after graduation?

230
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,120
If I'm not working at the plant,

231
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,250
I-I wouldn't know what to do back here.

232
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,440
Your dad, right?

233
00:10:30,910 --> 00:10:31,720
Mr. Ding.

234
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:34,720
And all the other uncles of yours.

235
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:36,800
They've spent their whole lives
at the plant.

236
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:39,060
Isn't that fine? What's wrong with that?

237
00:10:40,290 --> 00:10:43,170
Everyone knows everyone else inside out.

238
00:10:43,630 --> 00:10:45,510
If anyone runs into any problems,

239
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:48,870
they call for help,
and everyone will respond.

240
00:10:48,870 --> 00:10:50,400
Everyone will come to help.

241
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:52,290
How great it is!

242
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:54,980
Where else can you find
that kind of atmosphere?

243
00:10:58,390 --> 00:10:59,790
My mom says

244
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:04,550
some people are just sheltering
from the rain at the station.

245
00:11:06,150 --> 00:11:07,080
Some

246
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:09,840
leave in private cars.

247
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,120
Some

248
00:11:14,610 --> 00:11:16,260
leave on the bus.

249
00:11:22,310 --> 00:11:24,170
And some just stay where they are.

250
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,470
I'll miss you, too.

251
00:11:37,510 --> 00:11:38,860
Actually, what my mom says isn't

252
00:11:38,860 --> 00:11:40,260
necessarily right.

253
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,550
I think as long as we work hard,

254
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,410
we can all stay on the same train.

255
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,240
So, don't give up, Xiaoman.

256
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:01,680
Xiaoman, let's go. Xiaoman.

257
00:12:06,670 --> 00:12:09,000
Zhang Xiaoman, why aren't you answering?

258
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,980
Didn't we agree
to go to the sports school today?

259
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:13,630
I've got it in my heart.

260
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:15,390
I was just planning to go look for you.

261
00:12:15,390 --> 00:12:17,390
-Yet I fell asleep while lying down.
-Hurry up.

262
00:12:17,390 --> 00:12:19,360
I have to get home
before my dad gets off work.

263
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:19,870
Coming.

264
00:12:28,650 --> 00:12:30,350
Sir, I really don't need to do it?

265
00:12:30,350 --> 00:12:31,960
You really don't. Listen to me, Xiaoman.

266
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:32,820
Go on, Xiaoman.

267
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:36,040
How was it?

268
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,150
Wasn't it just a physical test?

269
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:38,410
Why did it take so long?

270
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:38,750
Well,

271
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,750
they got a student to fight me.

272
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:43,240
They were so rough.

273
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:44,170
Did you get hurt?

274
00:12:44,170 --> 00:12:46,430
I'm fine. I was wearing protective gear.

275
00:12:47,810 --> 00:12:49,200
What did the teacher say to you just now?

276
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:53,360
He told me not to bother
thinking about junior college.

277
00:12:53,970 --> 00:12:55,450
W-What does he mean?

278
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:57,360
H-How could he say that?

279
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,720
I think he makes a good point.

280
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,030
I don't think so.

281
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:01,720
L-Let's ignore him.

282
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,500
We'll turn to another... another teacher.

283
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:04,320
Someone with good judgment.

284
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,850
Why should we listen to him?

285
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:08,840
No, he asked me to go straight
for the sports academy.

286
00:13:12,230 --> 00:13:13,890
I knew you were the best.

287
00:13:16,980 --> 00:13:18,690
I don't want to go back to the plant.

288
00:13:18,690 --> 00:13:20,200
I want to stay here for a while.

289
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,130
Stay for a while?

290
00:13:21,270 --> 00:13:23,400
Okay! Then let's stay here for a while.

291
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:38,320
Xiaoman.

292
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:42,960
I've been giving thought
to the college entrance exam lately.

293
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,260
I was wondering

294
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:47,240
how to turn a hobby into a career.

295
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,300
I'm not good at math

296
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:49,180
or algebra.

297
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:50,970
I'm no good at geometry either.

298
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:52,420
But I'm good at drawing.

299
00:13:53,110 --> 00:13:54,800
So I wondered

300
00:13:54,870 --> 00:13:57,200
how to make a career out of it.

301
00:13:58,030 --> 00:13:59,630
Then I realized

302
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:03,720
I could go
for the architectural design major.

303
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:07,550
I-I could go to Shanghai

304
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:09,760
and apply to the Tongzhou University.

305
00:14:19,430 --> 00:14:23,760
How about you try to enroll at a college
in Shanghai, too? We could be together.

306
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:26,030
Are you applying to Tongzhou

307
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,700
because it's in Shanghai?

308
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:30,910
Of course not.

309
00:14:31,260 --> 00:14:34,520
It's because Tongzhou
has the best architecture program.

310
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:45,000
You don't want to go to Shanghai?

311
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,660
It's not like that.

312
00:14:49,150 --> 00:14:51,410
I know your family is moving to Shanghai.

313
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:58,630
I didn't actually want to go.

314
00:14:59,030 --> 00:14:59,720
But as you know,

315
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:02,630
I can't change my dad's decisions.

316
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:05,150
I definitely want to stay with you.

317
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:08,300
I want to be together with you
wherever we go.

318
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,550
And I didn't know how to tell you.

319
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:15,750
I thought I'd wait
until after the college entrance exam.

320
00:15:16,030 --> 00:15:19,230
We could just enjoy our time together
in these few months.

321
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:21,080
But you knew all along.

322
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,360
Chief Engineer Yan, what brings you here?

323
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,490
Go easy on the chili.

324
00:15:29,850 --> 00:15:31,180
Our family likes chili.

325
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:34,910
Mrs. Liu, going to buy groceries?

326
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:35,750
Yeah.

327
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:41,360
Xiaoman.

328
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,550
Welcome, Chief Engineer Yan!

329
00:15:44,550 --> 00:15:45,550
What brings you here?

330
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:46,630
Here, come on inside and have a seat.

331
00:15:46,630 --> 00:15:47,550
No need to go inside.

332
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,790
My wife cooked a few Shanghai dishes

333
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:51,270
and asked me to bring them to you.

334
00:15:51,270 --> 00:15:52,280
She wanted you to have a taste.

335
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,010
That's great.

336
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:54,150
She's so good at cooking!

337
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:56,870
Last time Xiaodan brought over
some steamed buns,

338
00:15:56,870 --> 00:15:58,070
I gobbled them all up.

339
00:15:58,310 --> 00:16:00,460
-Have a seat, please.
-I'm glad you like them.

340
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:01,090
Here.

341
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,960
Oh, God. Doing the big washing?

342
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:04,320
Yeah.

343
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:05,150
My school uniform got dirty.

344
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:06,550
Haven't washed it in ages.

345
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:07,810
Let me put this inside.

346
00:16:09,390 --> 00:16:10,990
Speaking of this courtyard,

347
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,530
I haven't been here
for more than a decade.

348
00:16:13,630 --> 00:16:14,960
It hasn't changed a bit.

349
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:17,550
Yeah. We were assigned
an apartment back then.

350
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:18,720
But my grandma didn't want to leave.

351
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,030
She just loved this place.

352
00:16:20,030 --> 00:16:21,750
So we didn't move and just stayed here.

353
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:23,480
Old people never like to move.

354
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,030
Well,

355
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:35,410
Chief Engineer Yan, did you come
to see me about something?

356
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:38,150
It's fine.
I just want to have a chat with you.

357
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:39,550
Chief Engineer Yan, I took Xiaodan
to Beijing this time.

358
00:16:39,550 --> 00:16:42,080
It was indeed us... messing around.

359
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:43,200
The families must have been worried.

360
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,320
-We two…
-Let's not talk about this.

361
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:45,050
We just decided and left.

362
00:16:45,050 --> 00:16:46,690
It's fine. Sit, sit down.

363
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,790
Where did you two go for fun in Beijing?

364
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:51,960
We didn't do anything fun.

365
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:54,100
We just w-went there for the competition

366
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:55,270
and came back right after.

367
00:16:55,270 --> 00:16:57,370
But the train ride back and forth
took a really long time.

368
00:16:57,370 --> 00:16:58,360
What a wasted trip.

369
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:00,560
There are so many fun places in Beijing.

370
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,720
The Great Wall, the Yihe Garden,

371
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:05,050
the Forbidden City, the Temple of Heaven,

372
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:07,280
right? And the Temple of Earth.

373
00:17:08,069 --> 00:17:09,200
Yeah, we wanted to go.

374
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,460
But we didn't have time during this trip.

375
00:17:11,550 --> 00:17:13,750
You can go next time
when you have the chance.

376
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:16,000
Time was indeed tight.

377
00:17:17,230 --> 00:17:18,490
You know, for you guys,

378
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:21,310
the college entrance exam is
only in a few months.

379
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:22,660
It's the same for both of you.

380
00:17:22,660 --> 00:17:23,790
Especially Xiaodan,

381
00:17:23,790 --> 00:17:26,400
she must focus on her studies.

382
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:28,830
Well,

383
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:32,790
there are way too many distractions
for her right now.

384
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:34,570
Let me name a few examples.

385
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,250
Like this competition,

386
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:37,200
right?

387
00:17:37,290 --> 00:17:38,420
Chief Engineer Yan.

388
00:17:38,540 --> 00:17:40,160
This was a legitimate competition.

389
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,550
It was organized by... by...

390
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:43,350
the Institute of Broadcasting.

391
00:17:43,350 --> 00:17:44,700
There were hosts all over there.

392
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,700
We checked it out.

393
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,480
It means nothing.

394
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,120
And for another example,

395
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,700
your influence on her.

396
00:17:53,350 --> 00:17:55,790
Xiaodan... Regarding Xiaodan's studies,

397
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,160
although I can't help much,

398
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,960
I haven't affected her studies.

399
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:02,400
About this competition,

400
00:18:02,430 --> 00:18:03,960
it's actually just a dream.

401
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:05,510
I... I wanted to take her to fulfill it,

402
00:18:05,510 --> 00:18:07,510
so she won't regret it in the future.

403
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:10,440
I didn't think too much about it.

404
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:14,960
I know you care about her.

405
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,730
Let me be straight with you.

406
00:18:18,550 --> 00:18:21,210
In these days
before the college entrance exam,

407
00:18:22,110 --> 00:18:23,310
I hope you can help her

408
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:25,720
as her friend.

409
00:18:26,550 --> 00:18:27,680
As for how to help...

410
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:32,110
I think you should understand what I mean.

411
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,370
I know, I know.

412
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:42,870
Well,

413
00:18:44,460 --> 00:18:46,350
do not affect Xiaodan's studies,

414
00:18:46,370 --> 00:18:49,570
and do not distract her.

415
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,190
Um,

416
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:54,570
she needs to get a good score
on the college entrance exam

417
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:56,060
and get into a good university.

418
00:18:56,060 --> 00:18:57,060
I... I know.

419
00:18:57,080 --> 00:18:58,080
Keep my distance.

420
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:00,480
It's a deal.

421
00:19:06,380 --> 00:19:07,580
Listen, Xiaoman.

422
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:10,480
You're not 18 yet,

423
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:11,720
but I see you

424
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:13,270
as a real man.

425
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:16,240
You know I like you very much.

426
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,880
So I think we had a good talk today.

427
00:19:19,350 --> 00:19:22,480
It was a good man-to-man talk.

428
00:19:22,790 --> 00:19:23,400
Right?

429
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:24,720
Of course,

430
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:26,400
since it's between men,

431
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:29,440
I don't want Xiaodan to know about it.

432
00:19:30,350 --> 00:19:30,960
Okay?

433
00:19:32,730 --> 00:19:33,820
I u-understand.

434
00:19:35,790 --> 00:19:37,990
After the college entrance exam, well,

435
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:40,590
you're welcome at our place anytime.

436
00:19:40,610 --> 00:19:42,890
You two can have all the fun you want

437
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,720
and do whatever makes you happy.

438
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,760
As for the future and the path ahead,

439
00:19:46,790 --> 00:19:49,190
the world is boundless. I won't interfere.

440
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:50,970
I understand, Mr. Yan.

441
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:51,430
Really?

442
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,030
I'll definitely support Xiaodan

443
00:19:53,030 --> 00:19:54,670
to do well on the college entrance exam.

444
00:19:54,670 --> 00:19:55,510
I-I'll help out.

445
00:19:55,510 --> 00:19:56,160
Good.

446
00:19:57,730 --> 00:19:58,930
Enjoy the dishes now.

447
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:01,090
If they get cold, it won't taste right.

448
00:20:01,180 --> 00:20:04,230
As Shanghainese say, the flavor is gone.

449
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,270
Alright?

450
00:20:06,310 --> 00:20:07,730
-Okay.
-You eat. I'm leaving.

451
00:20:07,730 --> 00:20:08,920
Let me empty the lunch box,
so you can take it back.

452
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:10,980
Don't bother. We'll handle it later.

453
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,030
I'm off.

454
00:20:13,050 --> 00:20:14,780
Take care, Chief Engineer Yan.

455
00:20:15,510 --> 00:20:16,440
Bye.

456
00:20:35,550 --> 00:20:36,550
Everyone, stay in your seats.

457
00:20:36,550 --> 00:20:37,700
The power will be back soon.

458
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:39,000
Forget about the power!

459
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,930
I'll be the first to run! Follow me!

460
00:20:42,310 --> 00:20:42,960
Don't go!

461
00:20:43,490 --> 00:20:44,890
Who said you could leave?

462
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:28,110
Why didn't you go?

463
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:31,490
You also didn't go, right?

464
00:21:39,310 --> 00:21:40,510
Then I'm leaving now.

465
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:56,290
Don't you want to ask...

466
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:58,960
where I'm going?

467
00:22:02,670 --> 00:22:03,800
Where are you going?

468
00:22:06,350 --> 00:22:06,880
Let's go.

469
00:22:16,980 --> 00:22:18,700
Hurry! You guys are so slow.

470
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:31,550
Don't push me!

471
00:22:32,030 --> 00:22:32,960
Run that way!

472
00:22:54,350 --> 00:22:55,680
She went to the rooftop.

473
00:25:08,900 --> 00:25:09,580
Sorry.

474
00:25:28,750 --> 00:25:29,590
Wait for me.

475
00:25:29,790 --> 00:25:30,650
Zhang Xiaoman!

476
00:25:32,150 --> 00:25:32,830
They said

477
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:37,070
you went to the rooftop
to look for me last night.

478
00:25:39,030 --> 00:25:39,830
Who said that?

479
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:42,510
Never mind who.
Just tell me. Did you go there?

480
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:44,270
Does it matter whether I went or not?

481
00:25:44,270 --> 00:25:45,730
Did... Did you wait for me?

482
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:48,290
Of course not. Why would I wait for you?

483
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:49,790
I'm asking you.

484
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:51,000
Did you go?

485
00:25:51,540 --> 00:25:52,390
No, I didn't.

486
00:25:52,750 --> 00:25:53,240
You...

487
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:55,400
Just admit it if you went there

488
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,800
and deny it if you didn't.

489
00:25:57,110 --> 00:25:59,030
I didn't go. I really didn't.

490
00:26:03,550 --> 00:26:05,010
Just keep being stubborn.

491
00:26:06,510 --> 00:26:07,240
So stubborn!

492
00:26:36,890 --> 00:26:38,440
Mom, Dad, what's the occasion today?

493
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:39,840
Why are there fireworks?

494
00:26:40,830 --> 00:26:42,350
Why was there only one?

495
00:27:10,890 --> 00:27:11,760
W-What?

496
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:14,300
You're not keeping your distance today?

497
00:27:17,310 --> 00:27:18,710
Were you home last night?

498
00:27:19,590 --> 00:27:21,200
Yes. Where else would I be?

499
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:24,050
Then did you see the fireworks?

500
00:27:24,830 --> 00:27:25,640
Yes, I did.

501
00:27:26,510 --> 00:27:27,640
It was really weird.

502
00:27:28,010 --> 00:27:28,680
They just went off twice

503
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:29,680
and then stopped.

504
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:33,680
I set them off.

505
00:27:35,350 --> 00:27:36,240
You did it?

506
00:27:40,110 --> 00:27:40,830
For me?

507
00:27:40,830 --> 00:27:41,980
Who else would it be for?

508
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:43,110
It was for you to see.

509
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:44,760
How was it?

510
00:27:46,750 --> 00:27:48,880
Is this your way of keeping me company?

511
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,400
Yeah. When you see fireworks,

512
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:51,730
you'll know I'm around.

513
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:55,070
What do you think?

514
00:27:55,070 --> 00:27:55,830
I like it.

515
00:27:55,850 --> 00:27:56,590
That's good.

516
00:27:58,090 --> 00:27:59,200
If you like it,

517
00:27:59,310 --> 00:28:00,970
then every Friday from now on,

518
00:28:01,110 --> 00:28:02,260
I'll set off fireworks for you,

519
00:28:02,260 --> 00:28:03,390
so you know I'm here.

520
00:28:03,590 --> 00:28:07,440
Okay. Then we have to set a time.

521
00:28:07,750 --> 00:28:09,280
Otherwise, I might miss it.

522
00:28:09,510 --> 00:28:10,770
Whatever time you say.

523
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:17,350
Then let's say 9:17.

524
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:19,350
9:17. Okay.

525
00:28:19,350 --> 00:28:20,490
That's easy to remember.

526
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:22,330
From now on, every Friday

527
00:28:22,590 --> 00:28:24,640
at 9:17 PM,

528
00:28:24,660 --> 00:28:26,860
I'll set off fireworks for you. Behold.

529
00:28:26,940 --> 00:28:28,730
Okay. I'll be waiting.

530
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:43,070
Xiaoman.

531
00:28:45,830 --> 00:28:47,510
Keep me company to the end.

532
00:28:51,790 --> 00:28:52,640
Deal?

533
00:28:57,750 --> 00:29:00,550
"Housing reform.
Are you really going to reform?"

534
00:29:01,050 --> 00:29:03,180
Look at the headline in the newspaper.

535
00:29:04,310 --> 00:29:05,840
Even they don't have a clue.

536
00:29:08,240 --> 00:29:10,570
Xiaodan has been behaving well recently.

537
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:14,210
She doesn't even take a glance
at such a good TV show.

538
00:29:15,140 --> 00:29:15,930
Sweetie.

539
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:19,240
Yang Zheng and Wen Hui are
back together in the end.

540
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:20,270
Stop it.

541
00:29:20,270 --> 00:29:22,310
Yes. They will definitely be together
in the finale.

542
00:29:22,310 --> 00:29:22,830
What's wrong?

543
00:29:22,830 --> 00:29:24,460
Our girl is studying. What are you doing?

544
00:29:24,460 --> 00:29:26,220
Who? Who is with whom?

545
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:27,920
It's "Cherish Our Love Forever,"

546
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:28,790
the TV drama I'm watching.

547
00:29:28,790 --> 00:29:31,050
With a mother like you, she won't do well.

548
00:30:01,270 --> 00:30:03,480
We haven't walked
side by side for a long time.

549
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:05,140
I wish it would rain every day.

550
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,350
I made an exception this time.

551
00:30:06,350 --> 00:30:08,310
I was worried
it'd be unsafe for you to go back alone.

552
00:30:08,310 --> 00:30:09,030
Go back.

553
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:12,590
Bye.

554
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:39,750
Get him!

555
00:30:42,610 --> 00:30:43,220
Beat him!

556
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:43,900
Beat him up!

557
00:30:48,630 --> 00:30:49,230
Get him!

558
00:30:49,250 --> 00:30:49,910
Beat him up!

559
00:30:58,270 --> 00:30:58,790
Get him!

560
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:01,460
Learn your lesson.

561
00:31:04,270 --> 00:31:06,350
Use this to hit him! Break his arm!

562
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:07,960
Hit him!

563
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:09,550
Xiaoman!

564
00:31:13,460 --> 00:31:14,590
Smash him to pieces!

565
00:31:18,950 --> 00:31:19,540
Boss!

566
00:31:21,830 --> 00:31:22,510
Xiaodan!

567
00:31:23,310 --> 00:31:23,960
Xiaodan!

568
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:25,830
Xiaodan!

569
00:31:26,110 --> 00:31:27,040
Don't come over!

570
00:31:30,310 --> 00:31:32,920
Let go of me! Let go!

571
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:37,270
Let me go!

572
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:38,790
Let go!

573
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:44,110
Let... Let go of me!

574
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:45,450
Let go of me!

575
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:46,750
Do you want to die?

576
00:31:52,350 --> 00:31:53,390
Xiaodan, run!

577
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:54,590
Run!

578
00:31:56,750 --> 00:31:57,720
-Boss!
-Boss!

579
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:02,350
Bro! Bro!

580
00:32:02,550 --> 00:32:03,280
Are you okay?

581
00:32:03,350 --> 00:32:04,370
Bro, wake up! Bro!

582
00:32:07,290 --> 00:32:07,820
Bro!

583
00:32:24,550 --> 00:32:26,960
Xiaodan, regarding what happened tonight,

584
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:27,960
if anyone asks,

585
00:32:28,330 --> 00:32:30,530
say nothing. I'll handle it.

586
00:32:37,070 --> 00:32:37,750
Come over here.

587
00:32:37,750 --> 00:32:38,880
You guys, come here.

588
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:39,880
What happened to you?

589
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:40,920
-Come here! Come!
-What's your name?

590
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:42,450
What happened to your face?

591
00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:43,400
What's your name?

592
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:44,600
From which district?

593
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:45,780
Come on, let me see.

594
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:47,480
Where are you going?

595
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:49,080
Which district are you from?

596
00:33:37,510 --> 00:33:38,160
Xiaoman.

597
00:33:39,390 --> 00:33:39,920
Xiaoman.

598
00:33:44,310 --> 00:33:45,910
You didn't sleep last night?

599
00:33:46,810 --> 00:33:48,070
What's wrong with you?

600
00:33:49,810 --> 00:33:50,570
What's up?

601
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:53,520
Did you not do your homework?

602
00:33:54,460 --> 00:33:55,020
Xiaoman.

603
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:56,500
Don't mess with me.

604
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:00,960
Who beat you up?

605
00:34:03,510 --> 00:34:04,350
Who did it?

606
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,990
What're you yelling about?

607
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:09,409
Come on, tell me who hit you.

608
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:11,760
No one. Nobody beat me up.

609
00:34:12,110 --> 00:34:13,110
I was boxing.

610
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:16,900
It got intense, and I lost.

611
00:34:22,230 --> 00:34:23,480
They are professionals.

612
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:25,280
There's no way you can beat them.

613
00:34:45,510 --> 00:34:46,150
Come on.

614
00:34:56,250 --> 00:34:57,580
What are you doing here?

615
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:00,420
Does your face still hurt?

616
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:02,990
It's scabbing over.

617
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,730
Don't wait for me after school.

618
00:35:10,510 --> 00:35:11,840
I've got a new job.

619
00:35:12,510 --> 00:35:13,840
We don't go the same way.

620
00:35:14,710 --> 00:35:16,370
Why did you get a new job again?

621
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:18,850
Aren't you going to apply
to a sports school?

622
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:19,360
Listen,

623
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:21,130
you still need to prepare
for your academic subjects.

624
00:35:21,130 --> 00:35:22,260
You can't skip that.

625
00:35:24,480 --> 00:35:26,080
I know. Don't worry about it.

626
00:35:30,670 --> 00:35:31,670
Did you hear that?

627
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:33,360
Did you hear the big news?

628
00:35:33,810 --> 00:35:36,120
Feng Xiaobo was beaten to death.

629
00:35:38,070 --> 00:35:38,690
Beaten to death?

630
00:35:38,690 --> 00:35:39,620
Beaten to death.

631
00:35:39,760 --> 00:35:42,000
There are assorted versions now.

632
00:35:42,150 --> 00:35:43,280
The rumors are wild.

633
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:45,550
Some say he was hit
in the back of the head with an iron rod.

634
00:35:45,550 --> 00:35:47,190
Some say he was stabbed to death.

635
00:35:47,190 --> 00:35:47,840
Others say

636
00:35:47,860 --> 00:35:50,120
Feng Xiaobo was killed
by a single punch.

637
00:35:51,020 --> 00:35:52,290
Killed by one punch.

638
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:54,340
There are various versions.

639
00:35:54,340 --> 00:35:56,060
Feng Xiaobo was a bad guy,

640
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,600
but he didn't deserve
to be beaten to death.

641
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:59,000
He was a terrible person.

642
00:36:01,110 --> 00:36:02,230
Who held such a grudge against him?

643
00:36:02,230 --> 00:36:03,050
I'll ask around for you

644
00:36:03,050 --> 00:36:04,380
and try to figure it out.

645
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:08,360
Do you know?

646
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:10,020
No, I don't.

647
00:36:13,070 --> 00:36:13,960
He's fine.

648
00:36:14,510 --> 00:36:15,960
Feng Xiaobo deserved it.

649
00:36:16,130 --> 00:36:18,550
-That was what he got for being a bully.
-Xiaoman.

650
00:36:18,550 --> 00:36:19,070
Ms. Tong.

651
00:36:19,070 --> 00:36:19,800
Come with me.

652
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:22,510
What's wrong?

653
00:36:22,510 --> 00:36:23,150
Nothing.

654
00:36:23,830 --> 00:36:25,060
Xiaoman, let's go.

655
00:36:33,510 --> 00:36:34,400
Oh, no.

656
00:36:35,150 --> 00:36:36,610
Xiaoman threw that punch.

657
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:39,070
Don't talk nonsense.
What are you talking about?

658
00:36:39,070 --> 00:36:39,800
Get the ball.

659
00:36:41,440 --> 00:36:41,960
Oh, no.

660
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:54,740
Talk properly.

661
00:36:55,450 --> 00:36:56,710
The police are inside.

662
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:09,340
Zhang Xiaoman.

663
00:37:10,830 --> 00:37:13,430
You should know
why I'm looking for you, right?

664
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,080
I know... I know.

665
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:26,400
I hit Feng Xiaobo.

666
00:37:29,670 --> 00:37:30,470
Director Hou.

667
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:34,150
Zhang Xiaoman is suspected
of intentional assault.

668
00:37:34,150 --> 00:37:36,120
I must take him back
for investigation today.

669
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:37,330
We failed to educate him well.

670
00:37:37,330 --> 00:37:38,590
Sorry for the trouble.

671
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:43,260
[Detention Certificate]

672
00:37:42,120 --> 00:37:43,120
Take a close look.

673
00:37:53,910 --> 00:37:54,620
Chen.

674
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:00,710
Officers,

675
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:02,200
Xiaoman is a good kid.

676
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:03,890
He couldn't have hurt anyone.

677
00:38:03,890 --> 00:38:05,280
We will investigate thoroughly.

678
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:05,810
Let's go.

679
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:12,110
Xiaoman.

680
00:38:21,150 --> 00:38:21,840
Xiaoman!

681
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:25,820
Tell the truth when you get there!

682
00:38:29,350 --> 00:38:30,810
Isn't that Zhang Xiaoman?

683
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:33,360
Zhang Xiaoman was taken away
by the police!

684
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:33,820
Come on!

685
00:38:37,970 --> 00:38:38,710
Isn't that Zhang Xiaoman?

686
00:38:38,710 --> 00:38:41,640
-Is that Zhang Xiaoman?
-It really is Zhang Xiaoman!

687
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:43,760
Xiaoman!

688
00:38:58,810 --> 00:39:04,730
♪ So many mountains I've climbed, rivers
I've crossed, trial after trial ♪

689
00:39:04,760 --> 00:39:09,980
♪ So many cliffs I've scaled, risky roads
I've walked, bend after bend ♪

690
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:16,820
♪ Through disasters I've caused,
hardships and hunger I've suffered ♪

691
00:39:16,850 --> 00:39:21,090
♪ The heart of the people
crossing the bridge rages like wildfire ♪

692
00:39:18,150 --> 00:39:20,190
Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

693
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:27,070
Xiaoman! Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

694
00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:28,500
♪ I've walked through dark alleys, hit
against high walls, fallen into the pond ♪

695
00:39:28,530 --> 00:39:35,060
♪ I've pursued my ideals, hated this body,
and been to the middle of nowhere ♪

696
00:39:30,630 --> 00:39:32,000
Xiaoman!

697
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:34,510
Xiaoman!

698
00:39:35,090 --> 00:39:40,320
♪ Gazing at the moon in a foreign land
in the gap of the city ♪

699
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:37,000
Xiaoman!

700
00:39:38,780 --> 00:39:40,020
Xiaoman!

701
00:39:40,480 --> 00:39:44,730
♪ Wishing only for the credit of one
who has crossed the bridge ♪

702
00:39:42,440 --> 00:39:43,920
Xiaoman!

703
00:39:46,650 --> 00:39:49,300
♪ Look at the river flowing ♪

704
00:39:49,330 --> 00:39:52,710
♪ Where will the young man
on the bridge go? ♪

705
00:39:52,740 --> 00:39:55,530
♪ The vibrant spring sees flying birds
and thriving greenery ♪

706
00:39:55,550 --> 00:39:58,090
♪ But my heart remains the same ♪

707
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,360
Xiaoman!

708
00:39:58,630 --> 00:40:02,520
♪ Listen to the wuthering wind
in the fog ♪

709
00:40:02,550 --> 00:40:04,780
♪ The one crossing the bridge
has no fear of the road ahead ♪

710
00:40:03,230 --> 00:40:05,270
[Western Tiecheng
Dongfang Affiliated Middle School]

711
00:40:04,800 --> 00:40:06,110
♪ With the figure fading away ♪

712
00:40:06,200 --> 00:40:08,620
♪ The reckless youth is gone from now on ♪

713
00:40:10,670 --> 00:40:12,210
♪ With the figure fading away ♪

714
00:40:12,230 --> 00:40:14,580
♪ The reckless youth is gone from now on ♪

715
00:40:25,870 --> 00:40:27,250
Sweetie, don't cry.

716
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:28,400
What happened?

717
00:40:31,070 --> 00:40:33,360
Xiaoman may look like a good kid,

718
00:40:33,550 --> 00:40:36,230
but he always hangs out with ruffians.

719
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:38,410
Mom, can you not say that?

720
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:39,960
He was just trying to protect me.

721
00:40:39,960 --> 00:40:41,360
Were it not for Xiaoman,

722
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:42,000
-last night...
-Enough.

723
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:43,280
Stop talking about it.

724
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:45,110
Do you know if word gets out,

725
00:40:45,110 --> 00:40:46,310
what people will say?

726
00:40:46,550 --> 00:40:48,410
Don't say another word, Sweetie.

727
00:40:53,770 --> 00:40:54,830
Hello? Who is this?

728
00:40:57,280 --> 00:40:59,510
I see. Thank you.

729
00:41:02,570 --> 00:41:03,970
So what's the situation?

730
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:08,110
He's not dead,

731
00:41:10,220 --> 00:41:13,380
but it's unclear how bad the injuries are.

732
00:41:16,550 --> 00:41:18,830
Then Dad, what about Xiaoman?

733
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:20,930
He won't be in big trouble, will he?

734
00:41:21,760 --> 00:41:22,480
Hard to say.

735
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:25,810
Although the other guy started the fight,

736
00:41:25,900 --> 00:41:27,280
and Xiaoman was forced to fight back,

737
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:29,140
he did injure that guy, after all.

738
00:41:29,480 --> 00:41:31,150
In the end, it's up to the police

739
00:41:31,150 --> 00:41:32,280
to decide how to classify the case.

740
00:41:32,280 --> 00:41:33,360
"How to classify the case"?

741
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:34,000
What else could it be?

742
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,510
Didn't Xiaoman hit him

743
00:41:35,510 --> 00:41:36,770
in order to protect me?

744
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:39,410
Why can't they classify that?
Just decide...

745
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:40,290
I'm going...

746
00:41:40,290 --> 00:41:41,840
I-I have to go
to the police station to testify.

747
00:41:41,840 --> 00:41:43,280
I'm going to testify
at the police station.

748
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:44,840
What are you going for? What for?

749
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:45,880
I'm going to testify!

750
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:47,880
Xiaoman can explain it
to the police himself.

751
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:49,210
It's no use for you to go.

752
00:41:49,770 --> 00:41:50,670
Nobody has died,

753
00:41:50,670 --> 00:41:52,400
but the rumors say someone did.

754
00:41:52,670 --> 00:41:54,710
If people say you were harassed
by those hooligans,

755
00:41:54,710 --> 00:41:55,710
what will you do then?

756
00:41:55,710 --> 00:41:56,860
I don't care about that!

757
00:41:56,860 --> 00:41:57,720
Does it matter?

758
00:41:57,800 --> 00:41:59,280
Xiaoman is already under detention!

759
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:00,190
You are a girl!

760
00:42:00,190 --> 00:42:00,840
He is a boy.

761
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:01,510
It's different.

762
00:42:01,510 --> 00:42:02,670
Come back. Get inside quickly.

763
00:42:02,670 --> 00:42:03,730
-Enough!
-Come in.

764
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:12,720
I'm going to the police station.

765
00:42:15,710 --> 00:42:16,550
Don't worry.

766
00:42:17,450 --> 00:42:19,310
I will report the facts you told me

767
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:21,550
to the police in full detail.

768
00:42:21,890 --> 00:42:25,000
We'll try not
to let Xiaoman be wronged, okay?

769
00:42:27,200 --> 00:42:28,110
Stay home and watch her.

770
00:42:28,110 --> 00:42:29,570
Don't let her go anywhere.

771
00:42:30,190 --> 00:42:30,800
Be good.

772
00:42:50,360 --> 00:42:53,320
Sweetie, I know you're anxious.

773
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:55,560
But there's no point in you going.

774
00:42:55,560 --> 00:42:57,810
Right? You're just a child.

775
00:42:58,710 --> 00:42:59,820
Going there won't help.

776
00:42:59,820 --> 00:43:00,380
Okay?

777
00:43:00,510 --> 00:43:01,960
Come on. Come inside.

778
00:43:02,470 --> 00:43:04,270
Alright, come in, Sweetie.

